abstract: Conservative Croatian Democratic Union wins 61 seats in country's elections, handing it most of any party; party, however, falls short of 151-seat majority, setting country up for long negotiations among coalition partners.

headline.print_headline: Conservatives in Croatia Get an Early Edge in Elections
headline.main: Conservative Party in Croatia Wins Parliamentary Elections

snippet: The Croatian Democratic Union captured 61 seats, more than the rival Social Democrats but short of a clear governing majority....
lead_paragraph: The Croatian Democratic Union captured 61 seats, more than the rival Social Democrats but short of a clear governing majority.
